description.narrative: The purpose of this Programme is to bridge the gap between investors and entrepreneurs through the Private Financing Advisory Network (PFAN) that will be hosted by the United Nations Industrial Development Organization (UNIDO) and executed in collaboration with the Renewable Energy and Energy Efficiency Partnership (REEEP). By successfully contributing to the development and deployment of low carbon generation capacity in a number of key developing countries, PFAN will in turn help to mitigate global emissions of greenhouse gases, and to achieve the goals of the 2016 UNFCCC Paris climate agreement, including mobilizing USD 100 billion per year by 2020 of private and public financing, PFAN will also help meet the 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development.
